Use clear, jargon‑free language, especially when discussing mechanisms of action or clinical trial phases; this reduces cognitive overload for non‑experts. Provide concrete examples—e.g., a 95% reduction in hospitalization among vaccinated populations—to illustrate real-world impact. When addressing myths, employ the “debunking” technique: state the myth plainly, then present evidence that contradicts it, followed by an explanation of why the misinformation persists (cognitive biases, social media echo chambers). Encourage questions and be prepared to admit uncertainty; saying “I’m not sure about that, let me look it up” can build trust.

